jobs.description:
Partner with Functional Director(s) within the Corporate Functions to provide strategic and specialist knowledge in areas of learning and development, employee engagement, talent management, reward & organisation effectiveness to contribute to effective business unit/function performance. This includes coaching and supporting leadership teams and driving organisation design to transform the objectives, structure, processes, resource, performance and capabilities of each function.

Responsible for the National ER/IR agenda including managing a range of performance management and disciplinary matters across the business, provide advice in handling employee claims including providing a wide range of stakeholders with commercial and practical interpretations of the Enterprise Bargaining Agreement (EBA), Fair Work Act 2009 and other related legislation. In addition this role involves designing and delivering on a number of people related projects across the business, including ER related training, and drive implementation of strategies for employment equity and diversity outcomes;

Maintain overall responsibility for the National WHS agenda but provide specialist advice to Leadership teams as functional owners of WHS as they drive and deliver the WHS strategy within their area.

I was responsible for partnering with defined client groups within Canon and owned responsibility for the delivery of generalist Human Resource strategy and operations.

This included working with management groups of all levels to build and implement HR solutions in-line with business strategy;

Managing the delivery of all Generalist HR activities covering multiple areas of HR, including but not limited to HR Planning, Organisation Effectiveness, Developing HR Managers’ HR Capability, Risk/Case Management, Business Change, Employee Change and Policy & Product Developments;

Supporting and guiding the business in HR excellence, enabling strategic direction, line management capability and driving corporate initiatives;

Offering expert advice and coaching to business leaders to deliver on going improvements in organisational effectiveness and to achieve desired cultural change;

Drive, project manage and deploy HR/L&OD projects and process improvement initiatives across the business.

